EVALUATION OF FOOD WASTE ORGANIC FERTILIZER EFFICIENCY ON THE GROWTH OF AFRICAN MARIGOLD (TAGETES ERECTA L.)¶

# Import necessary libraries for Analysis
import pandas as pd                      # Loading Data as a DataFrame, Descriptive Statistics

import statsmodels                       # Tukeys Honest Significant Difference

Inferential Statistics¶

scipy.stats.f_oneway()¶

In [62]:
# Will store the results of the Anova test 
# Then will be transformed into a data frame and
# Saved as a .csv file
Results = {
    "Growth Parameter": ["Height (cm)", "No. of leaves", "Total length of leaves (cm)"],
    "F-statistic": [],
    "P-value": [],
    "Rejected null hypothesis": []
}
In [63]:
# Anova test for Height 
f, p = stats.f_oneway(EG["Height (cm)"], PCG["Height (cm)"], NCG["Height (cm)"])
# Store results 
Results["P-value"].append(p)
Results["F-statistic"].append(f)
Results["Rejected null hypothesis"].append(True if p < 0.05 else False)
In [64]:

Post-Hoc tests¶

Bonferroni Test¶

In [101]:
# Find where the significant difference lies through t-tests
# Get all pairwise combinations of the fertilization treatments
pairs = list(itertools.combinations([EG, PCG, NCG], 2))
# Corrected Significance Level
corr_sig_level = 0.05 / len(pairs)
print(f"Corrected Significance Level: {corr_sig_level}")

Corrected Significance Level: 0.016666666666666666
In [102]:
# Find where the significant difference lies for the Height (cm) parameter
height_test =  {
    "Pairs": [],
    "T-statistic": [],
    "P-value": [],
    "Reject null hypothesis": []
}

for p1, p2 in pairs:
    height_test["Pairs"].append(f"{p1.iloc[0]['Treatment']} ~ {p2.iloc[0]['Treatment']}")
    # T-test
    t, p = stats.ttest_ind(p1["Height (cm)"], p2["Height (cm)"])
    height_test["T-statistic"].append(t)
    height_test["P-value"].append(p)
    height_test["Reject null hypothesis"].append(True if p < corr_sig_level else False)
    
# Convert to DataFrame
height_test = pd.DataFrame(height_test)
# Save as csv
height_test.to_csv("height_test.csv", index=False)
# View Results
height_test

# Tukeys Honest Significant Difference on Height (cm)
height_thsd = statsmodels.stats.multicomp.MultiComparison(df["Height (cm)"], df["Treatment"])
height_thsd = height_thsd.tukeyhsd()
print(height_thsd)

# Visualize the Heights of each fertilization treatments as a boxplot
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

b1 = ax.boxplot(EG["Height (cm)"], positions=[1], patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor="C0"))
b2 = ax.boxplot(PCG["Height (cm)"], positions=[2], patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor="C2"))
b3 = ax.boxplot(NCG["Height (cm)"], positions=[3], patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor="C4"))

# Set title
plt.title("Fig 1. Comparison of Height (cm) for each fertilization treatment")

# Set legends
ax.legend((b1["boxes"][0], b2["boxes"][0], b3["boxes"][0]), [
    "EG - Food waste organic fertilizer", 
    "PCG - Potassium Boron inorganic fertilizer", 
    "NCG - No Fertilization Treatment"
], bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.2), loc='upper center', ncol=3)

# Set labels
ax.set_ylabel("Height (cm)")
ax.set_xlabel("Fertilization Treatments")

# Save as png
plt.savefig("figures/fig_1.png", bbox_inches='tight')

plt.show()

plt.plot(x, EG["Total length of leaves (cm)"])
plt.plot(x, PCG["Total length of leaves (cm)"])
plt.plot(x, NCG["Total length of leaves (cm)"])

# set y min
plt.ylim(ymin=0)

# Set title
plt.title("Fig 6. Total length of leaves (cm) Comparison of each samples")

# Set legend
plt.legend([
    "EG - Food waste organic fertilizer", 
    "PCG - Potassium Boron inorganic fertilizer", 
    "NCG - No Fertilization Treatment"
], bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.2), loc='upper center', ncol=3)

# Set labels
plt.ylabel("Total length of leaves (cm)")
plt.xlabel("Samples")

# Save as png
plt.savefig("figures/fig_6.png", bbox_inches='tight')

plt.show()
